# EcoAtlas Architecture

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router with Turbopack
- TypeScript (strict mode), path alias `@/*` resolves to project root (`ecoatlas/`)
- react-globe.gl + Three.js for 3D globe (client-only, no SSR)
- Tailwind CSS v4, Radix UI primitives, class-variance-authority
- Zod for runtime validation (API responses, metric schemas)
- Vitest for testing (`__tests__/`)
- PostHog analytics (optional, env-gated)

## Directory Structure

```
ecoatlas/
  app/                    # Next.js App Router
    api/hotspots/         # Force-static API routes (list + detail)
    components/           # GlobeView.tsx, AnalyticsProvider.tsx
    globe/page.tsx        # Globe route
    page.tsx              # Home (renders GlobeView)
  components/             # Sidebar, MetricCard, Sparkline, ui/ primitives
  src/data/               # sourceMap.ts (metric catalog), schemas
  src/lib/schemas/        # Zod MetricValueSchema (series | snapshot)
  data/                   # Static data files
    hotspots.json         # 16 hotspots (id, name, lat, lng, severity, type)
    hotspotDetails/       # Per-hotspot story/sources JSON (hs-001..hs-016)
    series/               # Time series JSON per hotspot/metric
    metricsSnapshots.ts   # Fallback snapshot metrics
  scripts/                # Data ingest pipeline (fetchers, ingest.ts)
  __tests__/              # API, data integrity, schema, sourceMap tests
```

## Data Flow

```
scripts/fetchers -> data/series/ & data/hotspotDetails/
                          |
              app/api/hotspots/ (static routes, Zod-validated)
                          |
              GlobeView.tsx (client fetch + render)
```

## Key Conventions

- **Metrics** have two shapes: `kind: "series"` (time series array) or `kind: "snapshot"` (single value). Both validated by `MetricValueSchema`.
- **sourceMap** (`src/data/sourceMap.ts`) is the single source of truth for which hotspot has which metrics and data sources.
- **API routes** are force-static with `generateStaticParams` from `hotspots.json`.
- **Hotspots**: 16 total (8 drivers, 8 impacts), ids `hs-001`..`hs-016`, plus `hs-000` for global atmosphere (CO2). Severity 1-10. Type is `"driver"` or `"impact"`.
- **Driver** color = crimson/red. **Impact** color = blue. Accent green = `#4ade80`.

## Important Constants

- **Current year**: 2026 (used for timeline "Now" marker and initial state)
- **Climate Time Machine range**: 1990-2050
- **Climate Clock** (IPCC AR6 scientific reference, NOT the UI year): budget 250 Gt CO2, rate 40.2 Gt/yr, warming +1.29C, reference date 2024-01-01
- **Sidebar width**: 420px

## Testing

Run `npx vitest` from `ecoatlas/`. Tests cover:
- API response shapes and status codes
- Data file integrity (chronological, finite values, required fields)
- Zod schema contracts for metrics
- sourceMap consistency (all ids, paths, and sources cross-referenced)
